HD buffer question - 8mb or 16mb?

     My birthday is just around the corner, and was thinking of upgrading
     my all-purpose notebook with a zippier 5400rpm drive. I currently
     have a 60gb 4200rpm model installed, which is nice, but I see it as
     a waste of storage, since I don't want to store 60gb of files on
     something that's getting banged around all the time. Instead, my
     plan is to move the slower drive into a external drive holder (which
     I will also purchase at the same time) and use it as external
     storage and backup. This way I get the better file security while
     getting a speedier system. Now that I've got the "why" out of the
     way, here's my choices:
     Option 1:
     Hitachi 30GB 5400RPM 8mb buffer - $80.25
     Option 2:
     TOSHIBA 40GB 5400RPM 16mb buffer - $97.00
     My main question here is if the extra buffer cache is worth the
     extra money. I know 8mb is what all "premium" drives contain, but
     I've never been certain of what the HD buffer does. Would 16mb be
     overkill, or will it help performance and battery life noticably
     more than a 8mb model? I know it's only ~$17, but there's no sense
     in spending the extra cash if it won't make any difference.
     Note: I'm aware the Toshiba has 10gb more storage, but I really
     don't care about this, since I don't even use 10 GB of my current
     60gb drive. A 30gb drive should be more than enough for my notebook.
     My main concern is better performance.
     Thanks!
